1.Namespace and SFL
"Originally, the names of the C++ library functions, 
etc., were simply put into the global namespace (as they are in C). 
However, with the advent of the new-style headers, 
the contents of these headers were placed in the std namespace." 
Читаю шилдта и возник вопрос. Если имена функций SFL вложены в std, 
почему они всё равно находятся в глобальном пространстве
(т.е. к ним можно обращаться без using namespace std)?
--------------
SemiAnswer: 
<cstdio> header file will always import all its identifiers in the std namespace and maybe in the global namespace.
--------------
https://nsu-programming.github.io/textbook/env/setup-win.html
